3. Rent.com\n50: - **URL:** rent.com\n51: - **Company:** Rent Group Inc. (Redfin subsidiary)\n52: - **Scale:** Rental-focused platform\n53: - **Coverage:** Nationwide US, rental-exclusive\n54: - **Key UI Patterns:**\n55:   - **Landing Page:** \"Find your perfect place\" — image-based hero with search bar. Clean, minimal design.\n56:   - **Trending Properties:** Grid of property cards below hero with prices, price-drop badges, move-in specials (e.g., \"1 Month Free\").\n57:   - **Favorites:** \"Saved\" count in header, similar heart/favorite pattern.\n58:   - **Mobile-first:** Strong app download promotion with QR code.\n59:   - **Renter Blog/Resources:** Integrated blog for tips and guides.\n60:   - **Near Me Searches:** Prominent \"Apartments Near Me\", \"Houses Near Me\" shortcuts by bedroom count and budget tier.\n61: - **Sister Brand:** ApartmentGuide.com — nearly identical UI pattern, apartment-exclusive focus.\n62: \n63: ### 4. HotPads\n64: - **URL:** hotpads.com\n65: - **Company:** Zillow Group\n66: - **Scale:** Niche/map-centric\n67: - **Coverage:** Nationwide US\n68: - **Key UI Patterns:**\n69:   - **Map-first:** The map dominates the UI; property cards overlay as a scrollable list. This is the primary differentiator from Zillow's split-view.\n70:   - **Quick Filters:** Location-centric filters on map view.\n71: \n72: ### 5. Apartments.com\n73: - **URL:** apartments.com\n74: - **Company:** CoStar Group\n75: - **Scale:** Large commercial player\n76: - **Coverage:** Nationwide US, apartment-focused\n77: - **Key UI Patterns:**\n78:   - **Landing Page:** Search bar with location. Apartment-focused branding.\n79:   - **Listings:** Grid of property cards with community photos, starting price range, unit counts.\n80:   - **Property Detail:** Community overview, floor plans, amenities, resident reviews.\n81: \n82: ## Reference UI Patterns\n83: \n84: ### Universal Patterns Across All Competitors\n85: \n86: 1. **Prominent Search Bar on Landing**\n87:    - Every competitor places a large, central search input on the homepage. The default/primary input is location (city, ZIP, neighborhood). Zillow uses natural-language parsing (\"3 bedroom townhouse with fireplace in Seattle, WA\").\n88: \n89: 2. **Property Card Design**\n90:    ```text\n91:    +---------------------------+\n92:    |      [Photo / Carousel]   |\n93:    |                           |\n94:    +---------------------------+\n95:    | $1,995/mo   [heart icon]  |\n96:    | 2 bd · 2 ba · 1,200 sqft |\n97:    | 123 Main St, Austin, TX   |\n98:    | [Badge: New | Price Drop]  |\n99:    +---------------------------+\n100:    ```\n101:    - Photo is the dominant visual element (2:1 or 3:2 aspect ratio)\n102:    - Price is the most prominent text element (largest font, bold)\n103:    - Beds, baths, square footage on one compact line\n104:    - Address below\n105:    - Heart/favorite icon in top-right of card or inline\n106:    - Optional badges: \"New\", \"Price Drop\", \"1 Month Free\", \"Popular\"\n107: \n108: 3. **Search Results: Map + List Split View**\n109:    - Universal pattern: map occupies 50-60% of the screen (right side on desktop), card list scrolls on the other side\n110:    - Filters bar above results: Price (min-max), Beds, Baths, Property Type, More Filters\n111:    - \"Save Search\" button for email alerts\n112:    - Sort dropdown: \"Newest\", \"Price (Low to High)\", \"Price (High to Low)\"\n113: \n114: 4. **Filters Panel**\n115:    - Price range (double-ended slider or min/max inputs)\n116:    - Bedrooms (buttons: Studio, 1, 2, 3, 4+)\n117:    - Bathrooms (buttons: 1, 1.5, 2, 3+)\n118:    - Property type (checkboxes: Apartment, House, Condo, Townhouse)\n119:    - Amenities (checkboxes: In-unit laundry, Parking, Pool, Gym, Pet-friendly, A/C)\n120:    - Square footage range\n121:    - Move-in date / availability\n122: \n123: 5. **Favorites System**\n124:    - Heart icon on every property card (filled when favorited)\n125:    - Dedicated \"Favorites\" page/route\n126:    - Requires authentication to persist\n127:    - \"Saved\" count indicator in navigation\n128: \n129: 6. **Inquiry / Contact Flow**\n130:    - Contact form on property detail page\n131:    - Fields: Name, Email, Phone, Message\n132:    - \"Request a Tour\" or \"Contact Property\" CTAs\n133:    - Confirmation after submission\n134: \n135: 7. **Admin / Property Management Dashboard**\n136:    - Separate section or subdomain\n137:    - Key sections: Properties (list/manage), Inquiries (inbox), Applications, Leases, Payments\n138:    - Statistics overview (total listings, leads, recent activity)\n139:    - Table-based list views with actions (edit, delete, archive)\n140: \n141: ### Navigation Patterns\n142: \n143: | Element | Convention |\n144: |---------|-----------|\n145: | Logo | Top-left, links to home |\n146: | Main Nav Tabs | Buy / Rent / Sell / Mortgage / Manage (for Zillow), or Home / Search / Favorites / Dashboard (for simpler apps) |\n147: | Sign In / Join | Top-right |\n148: | Favorites | Top nav, heart icon or \"Favorites\" text |\n149: | Footer | City/state browse links, company links, app download |\n150: \n151: ## Page-type Conventions\n152: \n153: ### Landing/Home Page\n154: \n155: Standard sections observed across competitors:\n156: \n157: | Section | Purpose | Prevalence |\n158: |---------|---------|-----------|\n159: | Hero + Search Bar | Primary CTA: location search with optional text input | 100% |\n160: | Value Proposition | 1-2 line headline (e.g., \"Find your perfect place\", \"Your perfect rental one search away\") | 100% |\n161: | Trending/Featured Properties | Grid of property cards to demonstrate inventory | 80% |\n162: | Popular Searches | Quick links: \"Apartments Near Me\", \"Apartments by City\", \"Houses by City\" | 100% |\n163: | App Download CTA | QR code + app store badges | 80% |\n164: | Rental Resources / Blog | Tips, affordabilty calculators, market trends | 60% |\n165: | \"List Your Property\" CTA | Path for landlords to post listings | 60% |\n166: | Footer | City/state browse links, company links, Equal Housing logo | 100% |\n167: \n168: **NestFind Landing Page Recommended Sections:**\n169: 1. Hero with search bar (location + optional filters)\n170: 2. Featured rental properties grid (3-6 cards)\n171: 3. Popular cities/regions quick links\n172: 4. How it works (3-step: Search → Compare → Inquire)\n173: 5. For property managers: \"List your property\" CTA\n174: 6. Footer with city links\n175: \n176: ### Search/Listing Page\n177: \n178: Standard layout:\n179: \n180: ```\n181: +---------------------------------------------------+\n182: | [Search Bar: Location] [Price] [Beds] [Type] [Filters] [Save Search] |\n183: +---------------------------------------------------+\n184: |                  |                                  |\n185: |  Property Card   |                                  |\n186: |  Property Card   |          MAP VIEW                |\n187: |  Property Card   |                                  |\n188: |  Property Card   |                                  |\n189: |  Property Card   |                                  |\n190: |  [Pagination]    |                                  |\n191: +---------------------------------------------------+\n192: ```\n193: \n194: **NestFind Search Page Recommended Sections:**\n195: 1. Sticky search/filter bar\n196: 2. Filter sidebar or horizontal filter chips: Price, Beds, Baths, Property Type, Amenities\n197: 3. Sort dropdown (Newest, Price Low→High, Price High→Low)\n198: 4. Property card list (scrollable)\n199: 5. Map view (Google Maps embed with markers)\n200: 6. \"Save Search\" action\n201: 7. Results count (\"42 properties found\")\n202: 8. Pagination or infinite scroll\n203: \n204: ### Property Detail Page\n205: \n206: Standard layout from top to bottom:\n207: \n208: ```\n209: +---------------------------------------------------+\n210: | Photo Carousel / Gallery (full-width, ~400px high)  |\n211: +---------------------------------------------------+\n212: | [Back to Search]                                   |\n213: | Title: \"Modern 2BR Apartment in Downtown Austin\"   |\n214: | Address · Price · Beds/Baths · Sqft · Available    |\n215: | [Save/Favorite] [Share]                            |\n216: +---------------------------------------------------+\n217: |              |  [Inquiry Form]                      |\n218: | Description  |  Name: ______                        |\n219: |              |  Email: ______                       |\n220: | Amenities    |  Phone: ______                       |\n221: | Floor Plan   |  Message: ______                     |\n222: | Location Map |  [Send Message]                      |\n223: | Similar Listings                                     |\n224: +---------------------------------------------------+\n225: ```\n226: \n227: **NestFind Property Detail Recommended Sections:**\n228: 1. Photo gallery/carousel (multiple images)\n229: 2. Property title + quick stats (price, beds, baths, sqft, property type)\n230: 3. Key CTA buttons: \"Save to Favorites\" (heart toggle), \"Submit Inquiry\"\n231: 4. Overview / Description (rich text)\n232: 5. Amenities grid/list with icons\n233: 6. Floor plan image (if available)\n234: 7. Property details table (year built, parking, pet policy, laundry, etc.)\n235: 8. Google Maps embed (location)\n236: 9. Inquiry / Contact form (Name, Email, Phone, Message)\n237: 10. Similar/recommended properties\n238: \n239: ### Dashboard (Admin)\n240: \n241: Zillow Rental Manager model:\n242: \n243: ```\n244: +---------------------------------------------------+\n245: | Sidebar            |  Dashboard Content             |\n246: | - Properties       |                                |\n247: | - Inquiries        |  [Stats Cards]                 |\n248: | - Applications     |  Total Properties | Inquiries   |\n249: | - Leases           |  Recent Activity               |\n250: | - Payments         |                                |\n251: | - Pricing Tools    |  [Recent Inquiries Table]      |\n252: |                    |  [Recent Listings Table]       |\n253: +---------------------------------------------------+\n254: ```\n255: \n256: **NestFind Admin Dashboard Recommended Sections:**\n257: 1. Sidebar navigation: Properties, Inquiries, Users\n258: 2. Overview statistics cards: Total Properties, Total Inquiries, Total Users, Recent Activity\n259: 3. Properties table: Title, Price, Status, Actions (Edit, Delete)\n260: 4. Inquiries table: Property, Renter Name, Date, Status (New/Read/Responded), Actions\n261: 5. Add/Edit Property form: Multi-field form with photo upload\n262: 6. Inquiry detail view: Renter info, message, property link, respond action\n263: 7. User management table (view-only for NestFind scope)\n264: \n265: ### Favorites Page\n266: - Grid of saved property cards (same card pattern as search results)\n267: - \"Remove from Favorites\" action on each card\n268: - Empty state: \"No saved properties yet. Start browsing!\"\n269: - Accessible from main navigation (heart icon)\n270: \n271: ### Authentication Pages\n272: - Login page: Email + Password form, \"Forgot Password?\" link, \"Create Account\" link\n273: - Registration page: Name, Email, Password, Phone (optional)\n274: - Forgot Password page: Email input, \"Send Reset Link\" button\n275: - Clean, centered card layout (not full-width hero)\n276: \n277: ## Competitor Feature Matrix\n278: \n279: | Feature | Zillow | Redfin | Rent.com | ApartmentGuide | NestFind Target |\n280: |---------|--------|--------|----------|----------------|-----------------|\n281: | Property Search | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n282: | Location/Map View | Yes | Yes | Limited | Limited | Yes (Google Maps) |\n283: | Price Filter | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n284: | Bed/Bath Filters | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n285: | Property Type Filter | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes (apt only) | Yes |\n286: | Photo Gallery | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n287: | Favorites | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n288: | Inquiry/Contact | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n289: | Admin Dashboard | Yes (Rental Manager) | Yes | Yes (List Property) | Yes (List Community) | Yes |\n290: | Apps/Screening | Yes | No | No | No | No (MVP) |\n291: | Leases | Yes | No | No | No | No (MVP) |\n292: | Rent Collection | Yes | No | No | No | No (MVP) |\n293: | Mortgage/Buy | Yes | Yes | No | No | No (out of scope) |\n\n(End of file - total 293 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Domain Research\n\n## Industry\n\n**Industry:** Real Estate Rental Listings / Property Rental Platforms\n\n**Domain:** `nestfind.com` — Web application\n\n**Market Context:**\nThe online rental property market is dominated by several large aggregator platforms in the US (Zillow, Redfin, Apartments.com, Realtor.com). These platforms serve as two-sided marketplaces connecting renters searching for properties with landlords and property managers listing available units. The rental segment represents a distinct vertical from home buying, with its own user behaviors: shorter decision cycles, price-driven filtering, and frequent comparison shopping.\n\n**Key Differentiators in the Market:**\n- All major competitors aggregate MLS + direct listing data\n- Some are broader real estate portals (Zillow, Redfin) that cover buying, selling, renting, mortgages\n- Others are rental-specialized (Rent.com, ApartmentGuide, HotPads)\n- Admin/landlord tools are often a separate product offering (Zillow Rental Manager)\n- Map-based search is universal\n\n## Competitors\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1779174891329,"end":1779174891636}},"id":"prt_e3f1658e8001enpKefa47xDCZz","sessionID":"ses_1c0e9e840ffe9Rmyds03EgTY5k","messageID":"msg_e3f161bd1001qWZfGiOtCMUWGK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779174893712,"sessionID":"ses_1c0e9e840ffe9Rmyds03EgTY5k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_QAe4mISET4tpK8RLYMOP2788","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: ### Application Purpose\n6: \n7: NestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n8: \n9: The platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n10: \n11: ### Technology Stack\n12: \n13: | Layer | Technology |\n14: |-------|------------|\n15: | Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n16: | Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n17: | Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n18: | ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n19: | Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n20: | API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |\n21: | Validation | class-validator (backend), Zod (frontend) |\n22: | Frontend State | Redux Toolkit with createAsyncThunk |\n23: | Styling | Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI |\n24: | Maps | Google Maps API |\n25: | Deployment | Docker |\n26: \n27: ### Domain\n28: \n29: `nestfind.com` — web application\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## User Roles\n34: \n35: | Role | Description | Permissions |\n36: |------|-------------|-------------|\n37: | **Renter** | Browses rental property listings, views detailed property information, saves properties to favorites, and submits inquiries to property managers. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details`, `save_favorites`, `submit_inquiries` |\n38: | **Admin** | Has full system access to manage property listings (CRUD), manage user accounts, view and respond to inquiries from renters. | `manage_properties`, `manage_users`, `view_inquiries`, `respond_to_inquiries` |\n39: | **Guest** | Unauthenticated visitor who can browse public property listings and view property details. Must register/login to save favorites or submit inquiries. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details` |\n40: \n41: ### Authentication & Authorization\n42: \n43: - **JWT via httpOnly cookies**: Access token (1 hour) + Refresh token (7 days). Cookies configured with `httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'strict'`. Tokens are never stored in localStorage.\n44: - **Role-based access control (RBAC)**: Guards at the route/endpoint level enforce role-specific permissions via `JwtAuthGuard` + `RolesGuard`.\n45: - **Guest access**: Public endpoints for browsing and viewing properties are marked with `@Public()` decorator; all other endpoints require authentication.\n46: - **Admin assignment**: Admin accounts are created by existing admins or via database seeding. Self-registration defaults to Renter role.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Core Features\n51: \n52: ### Common (All Users)\n53: \n54: - **Authentication**\n55:   - User login with email + password\n56:   - JWT access token (1h) and refresh token (7d) via httpOnly cookies\n57:   - Token refresh mechanism with rotation\n58:   - Logout clears cookies\n59: \n60: - **Registration**\n61:   - Self-service sign-up with name, email, password, phone (optional)\n62:   - Default role assignment: Renter\n63:   - Email verification (optional, configurable)\n64: \n65: - **Password Reset**\n66:   - Forgot password flow via email\n67:   - Secure reset token with expiration\n68: \n69: ### Renter Features\n70: \n71: 1. **Property Search**\n72:    - Search by location (text input or current geolocation)\n73:    - Real-time filtering by price range, number of bedrooms, property type\n74:    - Results displayed as property cards with thumbnail, price, and key details\n75:    - Pagination or infinite scroll for large result sets\n76: \n77: 2. **Property Detail View**\n78:    - Full property page with photo gallery, amenities list, description, and floor plan\n79:    - Embedded Google Map showing property location\n80:    - Save to favorites (toggle)\n81:    - Contact / Submit Inquiry button\n82: \n83: 3. **Favorites Management**\n84:    - View all saved/favorited properties\n85:    - Remove properties from favorites\n86:    - Quick access from navigation\n87: \n88: 4. **Submit Inquiry**\n89:    - Contact form on property detail page (name, email, phone, message)\n90:    - Form validation before submission\n91:    - Confirmation message shown to renter\n92:    - Admin notified of new inquiry\n93: \n94: ### Admin Features\n95: \n96: 1. **Admin Dashboard**\n97:    - Overview statistics: total properties, total inquiries, recent activity\n98:    - Quick links to property management and inquiry management\n99: \n100: 2. **Property Management (CRUD)**\n101:    - List all properties with search, filter, and pagination\n102:    - Add new property with details: title, description, price, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, address, amenities, photos (multi-upload)\n103:    - Edit existing property information\n104:    - Delete or archive property listings (soft delete)\n105: \n106: 3. **Inquiry Management**\n107:    - View all inquiries with status (new, read, responded)\n108:    - Mark inquiries as read\n109:    - Respond to inquiries directly from the dashboard\n110:    - Filter by property or renter\n111: \n112: 4. **User Management**\n113:    - View list of registered renters\n114:    - View renter details and activity history\n115:    - Suspend or reactivate user accounts\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Functional Requirements\n120: \n121: ### Authentication\n122: \n123: - **FR-AUTH-001**: Users must authenticate with email and password to access protected features.\n124: - **FR-AUTH-002**: JWT access tokens expire after 1 hour; refresh tokens expire after 7 days.\n125: - **FR-AUTH-003**: Refresh tokens are rotated on each use (old token invalidated).\n126: - **FR-AUTH-004**: All authentication tokens are stored in httpOnly, secure, sameSite-strict cookies.\n127: - **FR-AUTH-005**: Guest users can browse properties without authentication.\n128: \n129: ### Property Search\n130: \n131: - **FR-SEARCH-001**: Renters can search properties by location text (city, neighborhood, zip code).\n132: - **FR-SEARCH-002**: Renters can use browser geolocation to find properties near their current location.\n133: - **FR-SEARCH-003**: Results support filtering by price range (min/max), number of bedrooms, and property type.\n134: - **FR-SEARCH-004**: Filters update results in real-time without full page reload.\n135: - **FR-SEARCH-005**: Each result card displays thumbnail image, price, address, bedrooms, and bathrooms.\n136: \n137: ### Property Details\n138: \n139: - **FR-DETAIL-001**: Property detail page displays full photo gallery with navigation.\n140: - **FR-DETAIL-002**: Property page includes description, amenities list, pricing, and property specifications.\n141: - **FR-DETAIL-003**: An embedded Google Map shows the property location with a pin marker.\n142: - **FR-DETAIL-004**: Authenticated renters can toggle the property as a favorite.\n143: - **FR-DETAIL-005**: A Contact/Inquiry button is prominently displayed.\n144: \n145: ### Inquiries\n146: \n147: - **FR-INQ-001**: Inquiry form collects name, email, phone (optional), and message.\n148: - **FR-INQ-002**: Form fields are validated client-side (Zod) and server-side (class-validator).\n149: - **FR-INQ-003**: On successful submission, renter sees a confirmation message.\n150: - **FR-INQ-004**: System notifies admin of new inquiries (in-dashboard notification).\n151: \n152: ### Admin: Property Management\n153: \n154: - **FR-ADM-PROP-001**: Admin can create new property listings with all required fields.\n155: - **FR-ADM-PROP-002**: Admin can upload multiple photos per property.\n156: - **FR-ADM-PROP-003**: Admin can edit all fields of an existing property.\n157: - **FR-ADM-PROP-004**: Admin can soft-delete (archive) a property listing.\n158: - **FR-ADM-PROP-005**: Property list supports search, sort, and pagination.\n159: \n160: ### Admin: Inquiry Management\n161: \n162: - **FR-ADM-INQ-001**: Admin can view all inquiries with status indicators.\n163: - **FR-ADM-INQ-002**: Admin can filter inquiries by property or renter.\n164: - **FR-ADM-INQ-003**: Admin can mark inquiries as read and respond to them.\n165: \n166: ### Admin: User Management\n167: \n168: - **FR-ADM-USER-001**: Admin can view a list of all registered renters.\n169: - **FR-ADM-USER-002**: Admin can view individual renter details and activity.\n170: - **FR-ADM-USER-003**: Admin can suspend or reactivate user accounts.\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Non-Functional Requirements\n175: \n176: ### Performance\n177: \n178: - **NFR-PERF-001**: Property search results must return within 500ms for typical query loads.\n179: - **NFR-PERF-002**: Image assets should be served with lazy loading and optimized formats (WebP).\n180: - **NFR-PERF-003**: API responses must use pagination for list endpoints (default: 20 items/page).\n181: \n182: ### Security\n183: \n184: - **NFR-SEC-001**: All authenticated endpoints enforce JWT validation via guards.\n185: - **NFR-SEC-002**: Passwords are hashed using bcrypt with appropriate salt rounds.\n186: - **NFR-SEC-003**: Input validation is enforced at the API boundary using class-validator/Zod.\n187: - **NFR-SEC-004**: CORS is configured to allow only the frontend origin.\n188: - **NFR-SEC-005**: Rate limiting is applied to authentication endpoints (login, register, password reset).\n189: \n190: ### Reliability\n191: \n192: - **NFR-REL-001**: Database operations use transactions for multi-step mutations.\n193: - **NFR-REL-002**: Soft delete (`deleted_at`) is used for properties and user accounts (no destructive deletes).\n194: - **NFR-REL-003**: API errors return consistent response format with appropriate HTTP status codes.\n195: \n196: ### Maintainability\n197: \n198: - **NFR-MAIN-001**: Backend follows the 4-layer architecture pattern: Controller → Service → Repository → Entity.\n199: - **NFR-MAIN-002**: All backend layers extend base classes (`BaseController`, `BaseService`, `BaseRepository`, `BaseEntity`).\n200: - **NFR-MAIN-003**: Frontend follows file organization patterns defined in `.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md`.\n201: - **NFR-MAIN-004**: All API endpoints are documented with Swagger/OpenAPI annotations.\n202: \n203: ### Compatibility\n204: \n205: - **NFR-COMP-001**: Frontend supports latest 2 versions of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.\n206: - **NFR-COMP-002**: Application is responsive and functional on mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports.\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Ontology / Glossary\n211: \n212: | Term | Definition |\n213: |------|------------|\n214: | **Property** | A rental property listing with details such as title, description, price, address, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, amenities, and photos. |\n215: | **Property Type** | The category of rental property (e.g., apartment, house, condo, townhouse, studio). |\n216: | **Listing** | A published property that is visible to renters in search results. |\n217: | **Renter** | A registered user who browses, searches, and saves properties, and submits inquiries. |\n218: | **Admin** | A system administrator with full access to manage properties, users, and inquiries. |\n219: | **Guest** | An unauthenticated visitor who can browse and view property details. |\n220: | **Inquiry** | A contact form submission from a renter about a specific property, containing name, email, phone (optional), and message. |\n221: | **Favorites** | A saved collection of properties that a renter has bookmarked for later reference. |\n222: | **Amenity** | A feature or facility available at a property (e.g., parking, laundry, gym, pool, air conditioning). |\n223: | **Soft Delete** | A record is marked as deleted (`deleted_at` timestamp) but remains in the database, allowing recovery and audit trails. |\n224: | **Archive** | A property listing that has been soft-deleted by an admin, removing it from public search results. |\n225: | **httpOnly Cookie** | A cookie that is inaccessible to client-side JavaScript, used to store JWT tokens securely. |\n226: | **Access Token** | A short-lived JWT (1 hour) that authorizes API requests. |\n227: | **Refresh Token** | A longer-lived JWT (7 days) used to obtain new access tokens without re-authentication. |\n228: | **RBAC** | Role-Based Access Control — restricts system access based on user roles (Renter, Admin). |\n229: | **JwtAuthGuard** | A NestJS guard that validates JWT from httpOnly cookies on protected routes. |\n230: | **RolesGuard** | A NestJS guard that checks user role permissions for accessing specific endpoints. |\n231: | **BaseController** | A base class providing automatic CRUD endpoints for controllers that extend it. |\n232: | **BaseService** | A base class providing automatic CRUD business logic for services that extend it. |\n233: | **BaseRepository** | A base class providing automatic TypeORM CRUD operations for repositories that extend it. |\n234: | **BaseEntity** | A base class providing UUID primary key, timestamps (`createdAt`, `updatedAt`), and soft delete (`deletedAt`) for all entities. |\n235: | **createAsyncThunk** | Redux Toolkit utility for creating async thunk actions for API calls in the frontend. |\n236: | **React Router 7 (Framework Mode)** | The routing system used by the frontend, where routes are defined declaratively using `route()`, `layout()`, and `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`. |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Architecture Overview\n241: \n242: ### Backend: Four-Layer Architecture\n243: \n244: ```\n245: HTTP Request\n246:     ↓\n247: Controller  (extends BaseController)  — HTTP handling, validation, Swagger docs\n248:     ↓\n249: Service     (extends BaseService)     — Business logic, rules enforcement\n250:     ↓\n251: Repository  (extends BaseRepository)  — Data access, TypeORM queries\n252:     ↓\n253: Entity      (extends BaseEntity)      — Database schema (UUID PK, timestamps, soft delete)\n254:     ↓\n255: PostgreSQL + TypeORM\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Frontend Architecture\n259: \n260: - **Routing**: React Router 7 framework mode with `routes.ts` defining `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` patterns\n261: - **State Management**: Redux Toolkit with `createAsyncThunk` for API data fetching; Redux slices per domain feature\n262: - **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod validation following shadcn/ui patterns\n263: - **Auth**: JWT httpOnly cookies with AuthContext, GuestGuard, and AuthGuard components\n264: - **Source Directory**: `app/` (not `src/`), imports use `~/` alias\n265: - **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + Shadcn/UI component library\n266: \n267: ### Directory Structure\n268: \n269: ```\n270: nestfind/\n271: ├── backend/\n272: │   ├── src/\n273: │   │   ├── core/              # Base classes, guards, decorators, filters\n274: │   │   │   ├── base/          # BaseEntity, BaseRepository, BaseService, BaseController\n275: │   │   │   ├── decorators/    # @Public(), @Roles(), @CurrentUser()\n276: │   │   │   ├── guards/        # JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard\n277: │   │   │   ├── filters/       # HttpExceptionFilter\n278: │   │   │   ├── interceptors/  # TransformInterceptor, LoggingInterceptor\n279: │   │   │   └── pipes/         # ValidationPipe\n280: │   │   ├── modules/           # Feature modules (entity, repo, service, controller, module)\n281: │   │   ├── infrastructure/    # External services (mail, s3, token)\n282: │   │   └── database/          # Migrations, seeds\n283: │   └── test/                  # E2E tests\n284: ├── frontend/\n285: │   └── app/                   # Source directory\n286: │       ├── components/        # ui/, atoms/, modals/, shared/, layouts/, guards/\n287: │       ├── pages/             # Route pages\n288: │       ├── services/          # httpService.ts, httpMethods/, httpServices/\n289: │       ├── redux/             # features/, store/\n290: │       ├── types/             # .d.ts per domain\n291: │       ├── enums/             # Synced from backend\n292: │       ├── contexts/          # AuthContext\n293: │       ├── hooks/             # Custom hooks\n294: │       ├── lib/               # cn() utility\n295: │       ├── utils/             # errorHandler, validations/\n296: │       └── styles/            # Tailwind + theme variables\n297: └── docker-compose.yml\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### API Base URLs\n301: \n302: | Environment | URL |\n303: |-------------|-----|\n304: | Development | `http://localhost:3000/api` |\n305: | Staging | `https://staging.nestfind.com/api` |\n306: | Production | `https://api.nestfind.com/api` |\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Related Documentation\n311: \n312: - [API Documentation](PROJECT_API.md) — Complete API endpoint specifications\n313: - [Database Schema](PROJECT_DATABASE.md) — Entity definitions and relationships\n314: - [API Integration](PROJECT_API_INTEGRATION.md) — Frontend-backend integration mapping\n315: - [Backend API Status](../status/backend/API_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Backend implementation tracking\n316: - [Frontend Screen Status](../status/frontend/SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Frontend implementation tracking\n317: - [Architecture Decisions](../memory/DECISIONS.md) — Key technical decisions log\n318: - [Coding Patterns](../memory/LEARNINGS.md) — Patterns and insights\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: seed.yaml + architecture guides*\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n\n## Overview\n\n### Application Purpose\n\nNestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n\nThe platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n\n### Technology Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|------------|\n| Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n| Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n| ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n| Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n| API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md","time":{"start":1779174893404,"end":1779174893710}},"id":"prt_e3f1660cc001XGNvYtrFEuQk08","sessionID":"ses_1c0e9e840ffe9Rmyds03EgTY5k","messageID":"msg_e3f161bd1001qWZfGiOtCMUWGK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779174895795,"sessionID":"ses_1c0e9e840ffe9Rmyds03EgTY5k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_7z29DIiM43h1bNg42vmv5782","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/skills/design/prd-to-design-guide/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/skills/design/prd-to-design-guide/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: prd-to-design-guide\n3: description: Convert PRD to Design Guide (used in both Path A automated and Path B external designer)\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # PRD to Design Guide - Generic Template for All Projects\n7: \n8: This is a **comprehensive reusable template** for converting any Product Requirements Document (PRD) into a Design Guide. Used in the fullstack pipeline Phase 3 (Design) as the first sub-phase for both Path A (Full AI Generation) and Path B (External Designer). The Design Guide serves as a human-readable review checkpoint before HTML generation.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## HOW TO USE THIS TEMPLATE\n13: \n14: 1. **Read your PRD thoroughly**\n15: 2. **Extract information using the tables below**\n16: 3. **Fill in the Design Guide template** with extracted data\n17: 4. **Follow the conversion patterns** for each section\n18: 5. **Output a complete Design Guide** ready for your designer\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## EXTRACTION WORKFLOW\n23: \n24: ### Phase 1: Extract Basic Information\n25: ### Phase 2: Define Design Philosophy\n26: ### Phase 3: Create Design System\n27: ### Phase 4: Convert Pages to Design Briefs\n28: ### Phase 5: Create Component Patterns\n29: ### Phase 6: Add Design Rules & Tips\n30: ### Phase 7: Create Deliverables Plan\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## PHASE 1: EXTRACT BASIC INFORMATION\n35: \n36: ### From PRD, Extract:\n37: \n38: | Information | Where to Find in PRD | Example | Variable |\n39: |-------------|---------------------|---------|----------|\n40: | Project Name | Title/Header | \"Crowd Builder\", \"MediCare+\", \"ShopEase\" | `[PROJECT_NAME]` |\n41: | Project Version | Version number | \"v3.1\", \"1.0\", \"MVP\" | `[VERSION]` |\n42: | Designer Name | Team section | \"Habib\", \"Sarah\", \"TBD\" | `[DESIGNER_NAME]` |\n43: | Timeline | Timeline/Deadline section | \"4 weeks\", \"2 months\", \"6 weeks\" | `[TIMELINE]` |\n44: | Project Type | App Type section | \"Web Application\", \"Mobile App\", \"Dashboard\" | `[TYPE]` |\n45: | Target Platform | Platform section | \"Desktop-first\", \"Mobile-first\", \"Cross-platform\" | `[PLATFORM]` |\n46: | User Types | User Roles section | \"Guest, User, Admin\", \"Patient, Doctor, Admin\" | `[USER_TYPES]` |\n47: | Total Pages | Count from Page Breakdown section | \"28 pages\", \"15 pages\", \"42 pages\" | `[TOTAL_PAGES]` |\n48: \n49: ### Page Count Breakdown:\n50: \n51: Count pages from PRD's \"Page Breakdown\" or \"Feature Specifications\" section:\n52: \n53: | User Type | PRD Section to Count | Example Count |\n54: |-----------|---------------------|---------------|\n55: | Guest/Public Pages | Common section, Public features | 6 pages |\n56: | Logged In User Pages | User features section | 13 pages |\n57: | Admin Pages | Admin Dashboard section | 9 pages |\n58: \n59: **Total Pages** = Guest + User + Admin\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## PHASE 2: DEFINE DESIGN PHILOSOPHY\n64: \n65: ### 2.1 Find Reference Applications\n66: \n67: **From PRD, look for:**\n68: - \"Design Reference\" section\n69: - \"Reference apps\" mentioned\n70: - \"What makes your app special\" section\n71: - Feature descriptions that imply UI patterns\n72: \n73: ### 2.2 Derive Design Inspiration\n74: \n75: **Pattern Recognition:**\n76: \n77: | PRD Feature | Design Inspiration | Reference App |\n78: |-------------|-------------------|---------------|\n79: | \"Upvoting system\" | Voting UI, ranking | **Product Hunt** |\n80: | \"Threaded comments\", \"Nested replies\" | Comment threading | **Reddit** |\n81: | \"Feed of items\", \"Professional network\" | Card-based feed | **LinkedIn** |\n82: | \"Dashboard\", \"Analytics\", \"Admin panel\" | Clean minimal dashboard | **Stripe**, **Linear** |\n83: | \"Stories\", \"Timeline\", \"Posts\" | Social feed | **Instagram**, **Twitter** |\n84: | \"Drag and drop\", \"Kanban board\" | Task management | **Trello**, **Asana** |\n85: | \"Chat\", \"Messaging\" | Messaging UI | **Slack**, **Discord** |\n86: | \"Calendar\", \"Scheduling\" | Calendar UI | **Google Calendar**, **Calendly** |\n87: | \"E-commerce\", \"Products\", \"Cart\" | Shopping UI | **Amazon**, **Shopify** |\n88: \n89: ### 2.3 Create Design Pillars\n90: \n91: **Based on key features, create 3-4 design pillars:**\n92: \n93: **Template:**\n94: ```\n95: **Design Philosophy:**\n96: \n97: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n98: 1. **[Reference App 1]** - [Key feature to study]\n99: 2. **[Reference App 2]** - [Key feature to study]\n100: 3. **[Reference App 3]** - [Key feature to study]\n101: 4. **[Reference App 4]** - [Key feature to study]\n102: \n103: **The [Number] Pillars:**\n104: - [Feature Area 1] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n105: - [Feature Area 2] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n106: - [Feature Area 3] = [Reference App] ([specific pattern])\n107: ```\n108: \n109: **Example:**\n110: ```\n111: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n112: 1. **Product Hunt** - Upvote buttons, card layout, ranking\n113: 2. **Reddit** - Comment threading, nested replies\n114: 3. **LinkedIn** - Professional feed, achievement feel\n115: 4. **Stripe** - Clean dashboard, minimal design\n116: \n117: **The Three Pillars:**\n118: - Feed = LinkedIn (professional cards, achievement vibes)\n119: - Comments = Reddit (threaded, vertical lines, indentation)\n120: - Dashboard = Stripe (clean, content-first, one action per page)\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## PHASE 2.5: DOMAIN & REFERENCE RESEARCH (MANDATORY)\n126: \n127: > **This step MUST be performed before generating the Design Guide.**\n128: > **Purpose:** Research the top products in the relevant domain to automatically identify standard UI patterns and essential sections.\n129: > **Instead of hardcoding a checklist**, discover \"what should naturally exist in this domain\" through research.\n130: \n131: ### 2.5.1 Competitor / Similar Product Research\n132: \n133: Perform WebSearch based on the industry and core features extracted from the PRD:\n134: \n135: ```\n136: Search queries:\n137:   1. \"[industry] best [product type] UI design 2025\" (e.g., \"design feedback SaaS best UI 2025\")\n138:   2. \"[competitor1] landing page\" (competitors specified in PRD)\n139:   3. \"[competitor2] dashboard UI\"\n140:   4. \"best [industry] web app design examples\"\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Research targets: Landing pages, dashboards, and core feature screens of the **top 3-5 products**.\n144: \n145: ### 2.5.2 Derive Standard Patterns by Page Type\n146: \n147: Extract **\"elements present in 80%+ of top products\"** from research results:\n148: \n149: | Page Type | Research Perspective |\n150: |-----------|---------------------|\n151: | Landing | What sections exist? (Hero, Features, How it Works, Pricing, Testimonials, Social Proof, CTA, Footer, etc.) |\n152: | Dashboard | What UI elements exist? (Search, Notifications, KPIs, Activity Feed, Tables, Quick Actions, etc.) |\n153: | Detail/Editor | What tools/panels exist? (Toolbar, Filters, Canvas/Content, Side Panel, Status Bar, etc.) |\n154: | Auth | What flows exist? (Social Login, Form Layout, Error States, Redirect, etc.) |\n155: | Settings | What sections exist? (Profile, Billing, Team, Notifications, Danger Zone, etc.) |\n156: \n157: ### 2.5.3 Deep Dive into PRD-Specified References\n158: \n159: If the PRD contains specific UI references (e.g., \"Notion-style Org Switcher\"), research the **actual latest UI patterns** of that product:\n160: \n161: ```\n162: Example:\n163:   PRD says: \"Notion-style Org Switcher\"\n164:   → WebSearch: \"Notion workspace switcher UI 2025\"\n165:   → Findings: icon + org name + dropdown arrow, \"+ New Workspace\" at bottom, search feature\n166:   → Reflect in the Org Switcher brief in the Design Guide\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### 2.5.4 Save Research Results\n170: \n171: Save to `.claude-project/design/{PROJECT}_DomainResearch.md`:\n172: \n173: ```markdown\n174: # Domain Research — [PROJECT_NAME]\n175: \n176: ## Industry: [Industry]\n177: ## Competitors Analyzed: [Product1], [Product2], [Product3]\n178: \n179: ## Landing Page — Standard Sections\n180: (List of common sections discovered from research)\n181: \n182: ## Dashboard — Standard Elements\n183: (Common UI elements discovered from research)\n184: \n185: ## [Core Feature Screen] — Standard Patterns\n186: (Common patterns discovered from research)\n187: \n188: ## PRD Reference Analysis\n189: | PRD Reference | Actual UI Pattern | Notes |\n190: |--------------|-------------------|-------|\n191: ```\n192: \n193: This file is **injected as context** during Design Guide generation and HTML generation, ensuring domain standards are followed without omissions.\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ## PHASE 3: CREATE DESIGN SYSTEM\n198: \n199: ### 3.1 Color Palette\n200: \n201: **From PRD, extract:**\n202: \n203: | PRD Field | Design System Color | Default if Not Specified |\n204: |-----------|-------------------|-------------------------|\n205: | \"Preferred Main Color\" | Primary Color | #0066FF (Blue - trust) |\n206: | Success states | Success Color | #10B981 (Green) |\n207: | Warning states | Warning Color | #F59E0B (Orange/Yellow) |\n208: | Error states | Error Color | #EF4444 (Red) |\n209: | N/A | Background | #F9FAFB (Light Gray) |\n210: | N/A | Surface (Cards) | #FFFFFF (White) |\n211: | N/A | Text Primary | #1E293B (Dark Gray) |\n212: | N/A | Text Secondary | #64748B (Medium Gray) |\n213: | N/A | Border | #E5E7EB (Light Gray) |\n214: \n215: **Additional Context Colors:**\n216: \n217: Look at PRD features for color usage hints:\n218: - \"Original ideas badge\" → Success color\n219: - \"Similar ideas warning\" → Warning color\n220: - \"Duplicate ideas\" → Error color\n221: - Status indicators → Map to success/warning/error\n222: \n223: **Template:**\n224: ```\n225: ### Colors\n226: - Primary [Color Name]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n227: - Success [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n228: - Warning [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n229: - Error/Danger [Color]: [HEX] ([Usage from PRD])\n230: - Grays: 50-900 scale (standard)\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### 3.2 Typography\n234: \n235: **From PRD, extract:**\n236: \n237: | PRD Field | Design System Value | Default if Not Specified |\n238: |-----------|-------------------|-------------------------|\n239: | \"Preferred Font\" | Font Family | Inter, SF Pro, Poppins |\n240: | N/A | H1 Size | 48px (hero sections only) |\n241: | N/A | H2 Size | 36px (page titles) |\n242: | N/A | H3 Size | 24px (section headings) |\n243: | N/A | H4 Size | 20px (card titles) |\n244: | N/A | Body Size | 16px (main content) |\n245: | N/A | Small Size | 14px (metadata, labels) |\n246: | N/A | Caption Size | 12px (fine print) |\n247: \n248: **Font Weights:**\n249: - 400 (regular) - Body text\n250: - 500 (medium) - Emphasis\n251: - 600 (semibold) - Headings, buttons\n252: - 700 (bold) - H1, H2, important headings\n253: \n254: **Template:**\n255: ```\n256: ### Typography\n257: - Font: [FONT_FAMILY from PRD or Inter/SF Pro]\n258: - H1: 48px (hero only), H2: 36px, H3: 24px, H4: 20px\n259: - Body: 16px, Small: 14px, Caption: 12px\n260: - Weights: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold)\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ### 3.3 Spacing System\n264: \n265: **Always use a grid system:**\n266: \n267: | Spacing Type | Value | Usage |\n268: |--------------|-------|-------|\n269: | Base Unit | 4px or 8px | Grid system foundation |\n270: | Card Padding | 20px or 24px | Inside cards/containers |\n271: | Section Padding | 32px or 40px | Between major sections |\n272: | Between Cards | 16px or 24px | Gap in grids/lists |\n273: | Input Height | 40px or 48px | Form inputs |\n274: | Button Height | 40px or 48px | Buttons |\n275: \n276: **Template:**\n277: ```\n278: ### Spacing\n279: - Base: [4px or 8px] grid\n280: - Card padding: [20px or 24px]\n281: - Section padding: [32px or 40px]\n282: - Between cards: [16px or 24px]\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ### 3.4 Component Specifications\n286: \n287: **From PRD features, identify needed components:**\n288: \n289: | PRD Feature | Component Needed | Standard Specs |\n290: |-------------|-----------------|----------------|\n291: | Login/Signup forms | Input fields | Height: 48px, Radius: 6px |\n292: | Submit buttons | Primary button | Height: 48px, Radius: 6px |\n293: | Cards/Lists | Card component | Padding: 20px, Radius: 12px |\n294: | Voting | Upvote button | Custom size based on prominence |\n295: | Images | Image container | Aspect ratio: 16:9 or 1:1 |\n296: | Icons | Icon size | 16px (inline), 24px (buttons), 32px (features) |\n297: \n298: **Template:**\n299: ```\n300: ### Key Components\n301: \n302: **[Component Name from PRD feature]:**\n303: - [Dimension 1]: [Value]\n304: - [Dimension 2]: [Value]\n305: - [Special feature]: [Description]\n306: - [States]: [Default, Hover, Active]\n307: \n308: **[Component Name 2]:**\n309: - ...\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## PHASE 3.5: VARIATION ARCHETYPE APPLICATION (Differentiating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEMs)\n315: \n316: > **This section MUST be followed when generating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEM variants.**\n317: > **Purpose:** Enforce that each variation has a visually completely different identity.\n318: \n319: ### Core Principles\n320: \n321: The PRD's design tokens (colors, fonts, icons) are a **functional foundation**.\n322: Each DESIGN_SYSTEM **freely reinterprets** these tokens to match the selected archetype.\n323: \n324: **NEVER do this:**\n325: - ❌ Apply the PRD background color (e.g., #F8FAFC) identically across all 3 variations\n326: - ❌ Use the PRD primary color the same way in all 3 (e.g., all solid buttons)\n327: - ❌ Only vary spacing/corners while keeping color/theme identical\n328: \n329: **ALWAYS do this:**\n330: - ✅ Apply a **different background color theme** to each variation (dark vs cream vs white, etc.)\n331: - ✅ **Interpret PRD primary color differently** (gradient glow vs pastel+accent colors vs sparse accent)\n332: - ✅ Apply shadows/borders/corners/typography weights **differently per archetype**\n333: \n334: ### PRD Token Reinterpretation Table (Examples per Archetype)\n335: \n336: This table is an **example**. Adapt appropriately based on the actual archetype combination.\n337: \n338: | PRD Token | Dark Vibrant Reinterpretation | Warm Playful Reinterpretation | Editorial Minimal Reinterpretation |\n339: |-----------|------------------------------|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------|\n340: | Primary color | → Gradient (primary→purple→blue) + glow shadow | → Solid primary + 4 accent colors (coral, teal, amber, lavender) | → Use Primary for CTA/active only, 95% grayscale otherwise |\n341: | Background | → #0B0F1A (deep navy dark) | → #FFFBF5 (warm cream) | → #FFFFFF (pure white) |\n342: | Card background | → rgba(255,255,255,0.05) + backdrop-blur (glass) | → #FFFFFF solid + warm shadow | → #FFFFFF + 0.5px hairline border only |\n343: | Sidebar | → Pure dark + gradient accent on active | → Warm dark purple (#1A1625) + colored icons | → Light sidebar (#F8FAFC) + 2px left border active |\n344: | Status Open | → #FF4757 neon + glow box-shadow | → #FEE2E2 bg + #DC2626 text (pastel pill) | → 6px red dot only, no text label |\n345: | Status In Progress | → #FFB74D neon + glow | → #FEF3C7 bg + #D97706 text | → 6px amber dot only |\n346: | Status Resolved | → #4ADE80 neon + glow | → #D1FAE5 bg + #059669 text | → 6px green dot only |\n347: | Border | → rgba(255,255,255,0.08) transparent | → #F0E7DB warm tone | → #F3F4F6 hairline 0.5px |\n348: | Shadow | → 0 0 20px rgba(primary,0.3) glow | → 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04) warm | → None (no shadows) |\n349: | Corner radius | → 12-16px (rounded-xl) | → 16-20px + pill buttons (rounded-2xl/full) | → 0-6px max (rounded-md) |\n350: | Heading weight | → 700 bold + tight tracking | → 600 semibold + friendly | → 300 light + editorial size (up to 4.5rem) |\n351: | Button style | → Gradient bg + glow hover | → Pill shape + lift hover | → Minimal border + subtle fill hover |\n352: \n353: ### Differentiation Verification Checklist\n354: \n355: After generating 3 DESIGN_SYSTEMs, compare the 7 items below. **5 or more must differ to pass:**\n356: \n357: | # | Item | A | B | C | Different? |\n358: |---|------|---|---|---|------------|\n359: | 1 | Background color theme | (dark/light/white/cream/gradient) | | | □ |\n360: | 2 | Shadow style | (glow/soft/none/hard/glass) | | | □ |\n361: | 3 | Border treatment | (transparent/warm/hairline/solid) | | | □ |\n362: | 4 | Corner radius | (3xl/2xl/xl/lg/md/0) | | | □ |\n363: | 5 | Typography weight | (700/600/500/400/300) | | | □ |\n364: | 6 | Status color expression | (neon/pastel/dot/solid/badge) | | | □ |\n365: | 7 | Sidebar theme | (dark/warm-dark/light/gradient/none) | | | □ |\n366: \n367: **Pass:** 5/7 or more → proceed\n368: **Fail:** swap archetypes and regenerate\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## PHASE 4: CONVERT PAGES TO DESIGN BRIEFS\n373: \n374: ### 4.1 Extract All Pages from PRD\n375: \n376: **From PRD's \"Page Breakdown\" or feature sections:**\n377: \n378: | PRD Section | Page Number | Page Name | Category |\n379: |-------------|-------------|-----------|----------|\n380: | Common/Auth | 1, 2, 3, 4 | Login, Signup, Forgot PW | auth |\n381: | Public | 1, 5, 6 | Landing, About, Browse (Guest) | public |\n382: | User Features | 7, 8, 9... | Dashboard, Profile, Settings | user |\n383: | Admin Dashboard | 20, 21, 22... | Admin Home, Queue, Reports | admin |\n384: \n385: ### 4.2 Convert PRD Page Specs to Design Brief\n386: \n387: **For each page in PRD, create design brief:**\n388: \n389: | PRD Element | Design Guide Format |\n390: |-------------|-------------------|\n391: | Page Name | **PAGE [N]: [Name]** |\n392: | Feature description | Brief one-line description |\n393: | Components listed | Section breakdown with components |\n394: | User actions | Implied in layout description |\n395: \n396: **Conversion Pattern:**\n397: \n398: **PRD Format:**\n399: ```\n400: #### 3.1 Login Page\n401: \n402: **Input:**\n403: - Email Address (required)\n404: - Password (required, show/hide toggle)\n405: \n406: **Next Action:**\n407: - Login button\n408: - \"Forgot Password?\" link\n409: - Social login (Google, Apple)\n410: \n411: **Rules:**\n412: - Email validation\n413: - Password minimum 8 characters\n414: ```\n415: \n416: **Design Guide Format:**\n417: ```\n418: **PAGE 2: Login**\n419: Split screen 40/60: Left (brand gradient) | Right (form: email, password, social buttons)\n420: - Email input (48px, mail icon)\n421: - Password input (48px, lock icon, eye toggle)\n422: - Login button (primary, full-width)\n423: - Forgot password link\n424: - Social buttons: Google, Apple\n425: ```\n426: \n427: **Shorthand Template for Pages:**\n428: ```\n429: **PAGE [N]: [Name]**\n430: [Layout type]: [Section 1] | [Section 2] | [Section 3]\n431: - [Key element 1]\n432: - [Key element 2]\n433: - [Key element 3]\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ### 4.3 Common Layout Patterns\n437: \n438: **Recognize these patterns from PRD:**\n439: \n440: | PRD Description | Layout Pattern | Design Brief Format |\n441: |----------------|---------------|-------------------|\n442: | \"Login/Signup form\" | Split screen auth | \"Split screen 40/60: Left (branding) \\| Right (form)\" |\n443: | \"List of items\", \"Feed\" | Vertical scroll list | \"List/Grid view: Cards with [elements]\" |\n444: | \"Dashboard\" | Sidebar + main content | \"Sidebar nav (200px) \\| Stats cards \\| Activity feed\" |\n445: | \"Detail page\" | Two column | \"Two columns 70/30: Left (content) \\| Right (sidebar)\" |\n446: | \"Form submission\" | Multi-step or single page | \"Multi-step progress bar \\| Sections: [list]\" OR \"Single form: [fields]\" |\n447: | \"Table/List management\" | Table with filters | \"Filter tabs \\| Sortable table \\| Action buttons\" |\n448: | \"Modal/Popup\" | Overlay | \"Modal: [trigger] → [content] → [actions]\" |\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## PHASE 5: CREATE COMPONENT PATTERNS\n453: \n454: ### 5.1 Identify Reusable Components\n455: \n456: **From PRD, look for repeated elements:**\n457: \n458: | PRD Pattern | Component to Define | Specs to Include |\n459: |-------------|-------------------|-----------------|\n460: | \"Idea card\", \"Post card\", \"Product card\" | Card component | Width, padding, elements, hover state |\n461: | \"Upvote\", \"Like\", \"Vote\" | Vote button | Size, icon, count display |\n462: | \"Comment\", \"Reply\" | Comment thread | Nesting, indentation, avatar size |\n463: | \"Stats\", \"Metrics\", \"Count\" | Stats card | Layout, icon size, number size |\n464: | \"Form\" appears multiple times | Form pattern | Input height, spacing, validation |\n465: \n466: ### 5.2 Component Pattern Template\n467: \n468: **For each reusable component:**\n469: \n470: ```\n471: **[Component Name] ([Style reference]):**\n472: - [Dimension 1]: [Value]\n473: - [Dimension 2]: [Value]\n474: - Elements: [List of sub-elements with sizes]\n475: - States: [Hover, active, disabled, etc.]\n476: - Usage: [Where it's used]\n477: ```\n478: \n479: **Example:**\n480: ```\n481: **Idea Card (Reusable):**\n482: - Width: 280px\n483: - Padding: 20px\n484: - Border radius: 12px\n485: - Shadow on hover\n486: - Elements: Avatar(48px), Title, Tagline, Thumbnail, Tags, Metrics\n487: - Usage: Browse page, Featured section, Saved ideas\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ### 5.3 Add ASCII Diagrams (Optional but Helpful)\n491: \n492: **Create simple visual representations:**\n493: \n494: ```\n495: **[Component Name]:**\n496: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n497: │ [Element 1]  [Element 2]    │\n498: │ [Element 3]                 │\n499: │ [Element 4 with sizing]     │\n500: └─────────────────────────────┘\n501: ```\n502: \n503: ---\n504: \n505: ## PHASE 6: CREATE CRITICAL DESIGN RULES\n506: \n507: ### 6.1 Extract Rules from PRD Features\n508: \n509: **Look for these in PRD:**\n510: \n511: | PRD Content | Design Rule |\n512: |-------------|------------|\n513: | \"18+ platform\", \"Age verification\" | \"Show age notice on landing, signup, footer\" |\n514: | \"Upvoting is core feature\" | \"Make upvote button HUGE and prominent\" |\n515: | \"Professional platform\" | \"Professional typography, generous whitespace\" |\n516: | \"Fast user experience\" | \"Loading states on all async actions\" |\n517: | Specific status (Original, Similar, Duplicate) | \"Color-coded status badges: Green, Orange, Red\" |\n518: | \"Mobile app\" | \"Mobile-first design, thumb-friendly tap targets\" |\n519: \n520: ### 6.2 Add Universal Design Principles\n521: \n522: **Always include:**\n523: \n524: 1. **Whitespace** - Don't cramp, be generous\n525: 2. **One Primary Action** - Per page (reduces cognitive load)\n526: 3. **Consistent Components** - Reuse design system\n527: 4. **Hover States** - Feedback on interactive elements\n528: 5. **Loading States** - For all async operations\n529: 6. **Empty States** - For zero-data scenarios\n530: 7. **Error States** - Clear, helpful error messages\n531: 8. **Accessibility** - 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum\n532: 9. **Responsive** - Mobile/tablet/desktop considerations\n533: 10. **Performance** - Optimize images, lazy load\n534: \n535: ### 6.3 Template\n536: \n537: ```\n538: ## Critical Design Rules\n539: \n540: 1. **[Rule from PRD feature]** - [Specific guideline]\n541: 2. **[Universal principle]** - [Application]\n542: 3. **[Platform-specific requirement]** - [Implementation]\n543: ...\n544: 10. **[Performance/accessibility rule]** - [Standard]\n545: ```\n546: \n547: ---\n548: \n549: ## PHASE 7: CREATE DELIVERABLES PLAN\n550: \n551: ### 7.1 Timeline from PRD\n552: \n553: **Extract timeline and create phases:**\n554: \n555: | PRD Timeline | Design Phases | Days Allocated |\n556: |-------------|--------------|----------------|\n557: | 1 week | Research & Wireframes | 1-2 days |\n558: | 2 weeks | Wireframes, Mockups | 3-5 days |\n559: | 4 weeks | Wireframes, Mockups, System, Handoff | 5 days |\n560: | 2 months | Full design cycle with iterations | 2-3 weeks |\n561: \n562: ### 7.2 Deliverables Checklist Template\n563: \n564: **Adapt based on timeline:**\n565: \n566: ```\n567: ## Deliverables Checklist\n568: \n569: **Day 1-2: Research & Wireframes**\n570: - [ ] Study inspiration sites ([list from Design Philosophy])\n571: - [ ] Collect reference images\n572: - [ ] Low-fidelity wireframes (all [TOTAL_PAGES] pages)\n573: \n574: **Day 3-[N]: High-Fidelity Mockups**\n575: - [ ] High-fidelity mockups ([N] key pages):\n576:   - [Page 1 from PRD]\n577:   - [Page 2]\n578:   - [Page 3]\n579:   - ...\n580: - [ ] Remaining pages\n581: \n582: **Day [N+1]-[N+2]: Design System & Components**\n583: - [ ] Design system (colors, typography, spacing)\n584: - [ ] Component library creation\n585: - [ ] Interactive prototype (key flows)\n586: \n587: **Day [N+3]-[Final]: Finalization**\n588: - [ ] Dark mode variants (if applicable)\n589: - [ ] Responsive designs (mobile, tablet)\n590: - [ ] Design QA, final polish\n591: - [ ] Handoff documentation\n592: \n593: **Final Delivery:**\n594: - [ ] Figma file with all pages\n595: - [ ] Component library (organized, documented)\n596: - [ ] Design system guide\n597: - [ ] Icon set (SVG exports)\n598: - [ ] Image assets (optimized)\n599: - [ ] Interactive prototype link\n600: - [ ] Developer handoff notes\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ### 7.3 Priority Order\n604: \n605: **From PRD, determine page priority:**\n606: \n607: **Criteria:**\n608: - Landing page = Highest (first impression)\n609: - Auth pages = High (entry point)\n610: - Core features = High (main value)\n611: - Admin pages = Medium (internal tool)\n612: - Legal/Settings = Low (necessary but not core)\n613: \n614: **Template:**\n615: ```\n616: **Priority Order:**\n617: 1. [Landing/Homepage] (first impression)\n618: 2. [Auth pages] (entry point)\n619: 3. [Core feature pages] (main value)\n620: 4. [Dashboard] (regular use)\n621: 5. [Admin pages] (internal)\n622: 6. [Settings/Legal] (necessary)\n623: ```\n624: \n625: ---\n626: \n627: ## COMPLETE DESIGN GUIDE TEMPLATE\n628: \n629: **Use this template structure:**\n630: \n631: ```markdown\n632: # [PROJECT_NAME] - Design Guide for [DESIGNER_NAME]\n633: \n634: **Project:** [PROJECT_NAME] [VERSION]\n635: **Designer:** [DESIGNER_NAME]\n636: **Timeline:** [TIMELINE]\n637: \n638: ---\n639: \n640: ## Design Philosophy\n641: \n642: **Core Inspiration (Must Study):**\n643: 1. **[Reference App 1]** - [Feature to study]\n644: 2. **[Reference App 2]** - [Feature to study]\n645: 3. **[Reference App 3]** - [Feature to study]\n646: 4. **[Reference App 4]** - [Feature to study]\n647: \n648: **The [Number] Pillars:**\n649: - [Feature Area 1] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n650: - [Feature Area 2] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n651: - [Feature Area 3] = [Reference] ([pattern])\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Page Count: [TOTAL_PAGES] Total Pages\n656: \n657: **[User Type 1] ([N] pages):**\n658: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n659: \n660: **[User Type 2] ([N] pages):**\n661: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n662: \n663: **[User Type 3] ([N] pages):**\n664: [Page numbers]: [Page names]\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## Design System Quick Reference\n669: \n670: ### Colors\n671: - Primary [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n672: - Success [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n673: - Warning [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n674: - Error [Name]: [HEX] ([Usage])\n675: - Grays: 50-900 scale\n676: \n677: ### Typography\n678: - Font: [FONT_FAMILY]\n679: - H1: [SIZE]px (hero only), H2: [SIZE]px, H3: [SIZE]px, H4: [SIZE]px\n680: - Body: [SIZE]px, Small: [SIZE]px, Caption: [SIZE]px\n681: - Weights: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold)\n682: \n683: ### Spacing\n684: - Base: [BASE_UNIT] grid\n685: - Card padding: [VALUE]\n686: - Section padding: [VALUE]\n687: - Between cards: [VALUE]\n688: \n689: ### Key Components\n690: \n691: **[Component 1 Name]:**\n692: - [Spec 1]: [Value]\n693: - [Spec 2]: [Value]\n694: - [Usage]: [Where used]\n695: \n696: **[Component 2 Name]:**\n697: - [Spec 1]: [Value]\n698: - [Spec 2]: [Value]\n699: \n700: ---\n701: \n702: ## Page-by-Page Design Brief\n703: \n704: ### [USER_TYPE_1] PAGES\n705: \n706: **PAGE 1: [Page Name]**\n707: [Layout description]: [Section 1] | [Section 2] | [Section 3]\n708: - [Key element 1]\n709: - [Key element 2]\n710: - [Key element 3]\n711: \n712: **PAGE 2: [Page Name]**\n713: [Layout description]\n714: - [Elements]\n715: \n716: ### [USER_TYPE_2] PAGES\n717: \n718: **PAGE [N]: [Page Name]**\n719: [Layout description]\n720: - [Elements]\n721: \n722: ### [USER_TYPE_3] PAGES\n723: \n724: **PAGE [N]: [Page Name]**\n725: [Layout description]\n726: - [Elements]\n727: \n728: ---\n729: \n730: ## Critical Design Rules\n731: \n732: 1. **[Rule 1]** - [Description]\n733: 2. **[Rule 2]** - [Description]\n734: 3. **[Rule 3]** - [Description]\n735: ...\n736: 10. **[Rule 10]** - [Description]\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## Component Patterns\n741: \n742: ### [Component 1] (Reusable)\n743: ```\n744: [ASCII diagram if helpful]\n745: ```\n746: - [Specs]\n747: - [Elements]\n748: - [Usage]\n749: \n750: ### [Component 2]\n751: ```\n752: [ASCII diagram if helpful]\n753: ```\n754: - [Specs]\n755: \n756: ---\n757: \n758: ## Deliverables Checklist\n759: \n760: **Day 1-2:**\n761: - [ ] [Tasks]\n762: \n763: **Day 3-[N]:**\n764: - [ ] [Tasks]\n765: \n766: **Day [N+1]:**\n767: - [ ] [Tasks]\n768: \n769: **Final Delivery:**\n770: - [ ] Figma file\n771: - [ ] Component library\n772: - [ ] Design system guide\n773: - [ ] Assets\n774: - [ ] Prototype\n775: - [ ] Handoff docs\n776: \n777: ---\n778: \n779: ## Design Tips\n780: \n781: 1. **Consistency First** - Use design system components everywhere\n782: 2. **Accessibility** - 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum\n783: 3. **Performance** - Optimize images, use SVG icons\n784: 4. **Responsive** - [Desktop/Mobile]-first approach\n785: 5. **States** - Loading, empty, error for everything\n786: 6. **Real Content** - Use realistic text, not Lorem Ipsum\n787: 7. **Whitespace** - Generous spacing\n788: 8. **Hierarchy** - Clear visual importance\n789: 9. **Feedback** - User knows what's happening\n790: 10. **Polish** - Subtle animations, consistent shadows\n791: \n792: ---\n793: \n794: ## Success Criteria\n795: \n796: Your design succeeds if:\n797: - ✅ [Feature 1] looks like [Reference App] ([pattern])\n798: - ✅ [Feature 2] feels [adjective]\n799: - ✅ Users can [core action] easily\n800: - ✅ Platform feels [brand adjective - professional/playful/trustworthy]\n801: - ✅ All [TOTAL_PAGES] pages designed\n802: - ✅ Component library complete\n803: - ✅ Responsive at all breakpoints\n804: \n805: ---\n806: \n807: **Priority Order:**\n808: 1. [Page 1] (reason)\n809: 2. [Page 2] (reason)\n810: 3. [Page 3] (reason)\n811: 4. [Page 4] (reason)\n812: 5. [Page 5] (reason)\n813: \n814: Good luck! 🎨🚀\n815: ```\n816: \n817: ---\n818: \n819: ## CONVERSION EXAMPLES\n820: \n821: ### Example 1: Login Page\n822: \n823: **PRD Input:**\n824: ```\n825: #### 2.1 Login Page\n826: \n827: **Input:**\n828: - Email Address (required)\n829: - Password (required)\n830: - Show/hide password toggle\n831: \n832: **Actions:**\n833: - Login button (primary)\n834: - \"Forgot Password?\" link\n835: - Social login: Google, Apple\n836: \n837: **Next:**\n838: - Success → Dashboard\n839: - Error → Show message\n840: ```\n841: \n842: **Design Guide Output:**\n843: ```\n844: **PAGE 2: Login**\n845: Split screen 40/60: Left (brand gradient) | Right (form: email, password, social buttons)\n846: \n847: Elements:\n848: - Email input (48px height, mail icon)\n849: - Password input (48px height, lock icon, eye toggle)\n850: - Login button (primary, full-width, 48px)\n851: - \"Forgot Password?\" link (below form)\n852: - Divider: \"Or continue with\"\n853: - Social buttons: Google (white bg), Apple (black bg)\n854: ```\n855: \n856: ### Example 2: Dashboard\n857: \n858: **PRD Input:**\n859: ```\n860: #### 5.1 Admin Dashboard\n861: \n862: **Sidebar Navigation:**\n863: 1. Overview\n864: 2. Pending Approvals\n865: 3. Reports\n866: 4. Settings\n867: \n868: **Main Content:**\n869: - Stats cards (4 metrics)\n870: - Recent activity feed\n871: - Quick actions\n872: ```\n873: \n874: **Design Guide Output:**\n875: ```\n876: **PAGE 20: Admin Home**\n877: Sidebar nav (200px, collapsible) | Stats cards (4 across) | Activity feed | Quick actions\n878: \n879: Layout:\n880: - Sidebar: Navigation items, icons 20px, active state with primary color\n881: - Stats cards: Icon 32px, metric 32px bold, label 14px gray\n882: - Activity feed: Timeline style, avatar 32px, timestamp\n883: - Quick actions: Button row at top\n884: ```\n885: \n886: ### Example 3: Form Submission\n887: \n888: **PRD Input:**\n889: ```\n890: #### 3.2 Submit Idea\n891: \n892: **Step 1: Basic Info**\n893: - Project Name (max 100 chars)\n894: - Tagline (max 150 chars)\n895: - Category (dropdown)\n896: \n897: **Step 2: Story**\n898: - Rich text editor (max 5000 chars)\n899: \n900: **Step 3: SWOT Analysis**\n901: - Strengths, Weaknesses, Opportunities, Threats\n902: \n903: **Step 4: Media**\n904: - Upload images (max 5)\n905: - Upload video OR YouTube link\n906: ```\n907: \n908: **Design Guide Output:**\n909: ```\n910: **PAGE 8: Submit Idea**\n911: Multi-step progress bar | Sections: Basic Info | Story (rich editor) | SWOT (2x2 grid) | Media upload | Actions\n912: \n913: Progress bar: 5 steps, show completion, click to navigate completed steps\n914: - Step 1: Project name input, tagline input, category dropdown\n915: - Step 2: Rich text editor (400px height, char counter)\n916: - Step 3: SWOT grid (2x2, equal quadrants, textarea each)\n917: - Step 4: Image uploader (drag-drop, preview grid), video upload/URL\n918: - Actions: Back, Next/Submit buttons (bottom, full-width on mobile)\n919: ```\n920: \n921: ---\n922: \n923: ## QUICK REFERENCE CHECKLIST\n924: \n925: **Before starting conversion:**\n926: - [ ] PRD read completely\n927: - [ ] Project name, timeline, designer extracted\n928: - [ ] All pages counted\n929: - [ ] User types identified\n930: \n931: **Phase 1 - Basic Info:**\n932: - [ ] Project metadata extracted\n933: - [ ] Page count calculated\n934: - [ ] User types listed\n935: \n936: **Phase 2 - Design Philosophy:**\n937: - [ ] Reference apps identified from features\n938: - [ ] Design pillars created (3-4)\n939: - [ ] Inspiration mapped to features\n940: \n941: **Phase 3 - Design System:**\n942: - [ ] Colors defined (primary, success, warning, error + neutrals)\n943: - [ ] Typography specified (font, sizes, weights)\n944: - [ ] Spacing system created (base unit, padding, gaps)\n945: - [ ] Component specs started\n946: \n947: **Phase 4 - Page Conversion:**\n948: - [ ] All pages from PRD listed\n949: - [ ] Each page converted to shorthand design brief\n950: - [ ] Layout patterns identified\n951: - [ ] Key elements listed\n952: \n953: **Phase 5 - Component Patterns:**\n954: - [ ] Reusable components identified\n955: - [ ] Specs for each component\n956: - [ ] ASCII diagrams (optional)\n957: - [ ] Usage notes\n958: \n959: **Phase 6 - Design Rules:**\n960: - [ ] PRD-specific rules extracted\n961: - [ ] Universal principles added\n962: - [ ] Platform requirements noted\n963: \n964: **Phase 7 - Deliverables:**\n965: - [ ] Timeline converted to phases\n966: - [ ] Checklist created\n967: - [ ] Priority order defined\n968: - [ ] Success criteria listed\n969: \n970: **Final Review:**\n971: - [ ] All [PLACEHOLDERS] filled\n972: - [ ] Page count matches PRD\n973: - [ ] Design philosophy makes sense\n974: - [ ] Component patterns are reusable\n975: - [ ] Design Guide is actionable for designer\n976: \n977: ---\n978: \n979: ## OUTPUT FILE\n980: \n981: **Save as:**\n982: - **Filename:** `[ProjectName]_DesignGuide_[YYMMDD].md`\n983: - **Location:** `.claude-project/design/` or project root\n984: - **Format:** Markdown (.md)\n985: \n986: **Share with:**\n987: - Designer (primary recipient)\n988: - Developer (for context)\n989: - Project Manager (for timeline)\n990: \n991: ---\n992: \n993: **Template Version:** 1.0\n994: **Created:** January 15, 2026\n995: **Purpose:** Convert any PRD to Design Guide\n996: **Reusable:** Yes, for all projects\n\n(End of file - total 996 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: prd-to-design-guide\ndescription: Convert PRD to Design Guide (used in both Path A automated and Path B external designer)\n---\n\n# PRD to Design Guide - Generic Template for All Projects\n\nThis is a **comprehensive reusable template** for converting any Product Requirements Document (PRD) into a Design Guide. Used in the fullstack pipeline Phase 3 (Design) as the first sub-phase for both Path A (Full AI Generation) and Path B (External Designer). The Design Guide serves as a human-readable review checkpoint before HTML generation.\n\n---\n\n## HOW TO USE THIS TEMPLATE\n\n1. **Read your PRD thoroughly**\n2. **Extract information using the tables below**\n3. **Fill in the Design Guide template** with extracted data\n4. **Follow the conversion patterns** for each section\n5. **Output a complete Design Guide** ready for your designer\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/skills/design/prd-to-design-guide/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1779174895513,"end":1779174895793}},"id":"prt_e3f1668ea001IrhnmmPbzQtmi6","sessionID":"ses_1c0e9e840ffe9Rmyds03EgTY5k","messageID":"msg_e3f161bd1001qWZfGiOtCMUWGK"}}
